articles.title: China stocks rise, brushing off weak GDP data - CNBC
articles.description: The Asian giant also kept its benchmark lending rates unchanged, in line with expectations, with the one-year loan prime rate at 3%.
articles.content:
Asia-Pacific markets opened higher Monday as investors parsed the latest slew of economic data out of China.
